java.lang.Object

public class Selenium2Wrapper

retryUntilTimeout

public boolean retryUntilTimeout(ConditionCheck condition)
Retries to evaluate the condition. If evaluation is successful, the method will return regularly. If not, this method will retry it with pauses until a timeout is exceeded.

Parameters:
condition - which will be evaluated on each retry
Returns:
true, if the condition could be executed successfully; otherwise false will be returned.

retryUntilTimeout

public boolean retryUntilTimeout(ConditionCheck condition,
                                 long timeout)
Retries to evaluate the condition. If evaluation is successful, the method will return regularly. If not, this method will retry it with a configured pause between retries until a given timeout is exceeded.

Parameters:
condition - which will be evaluated on each retry
timeout - how long will be waited
Returns:
true if the condition could be executed successfully; otherwise, false will be returned.
